From: Hien Huynh <hien.huynh.px@renesas.com>
Date: Tue, 10 Mar 2020 11:06:41 +0700
Subject: [PATCH 190/350] mmc: renesas_sdhi_core: Disable check SCC error in
 some modes

There is no need to check SCC error in some modes which excludes:
- HS400 4TAP.
- High speed mode.
- UHS-SDR50 mode.

Signed-off-by: Hien Huynh <hien.huynh.px@renesas.com>
---
 drivers/mmc/host/renesas_sdhi_core.c | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/mmc/host/renesas_sdhi_core.c b/drivers/mmc/host/renesas_sdhi_core.c
index 285d988..0ecb08b 100644
--- a/drivers/mmc/host/renesas_sdhi_core.c
+++ b/drivers/mmc/host/renesas_sdhi_core.c
@@ -452,6 +452,12 @@ static bool renesas_sdhi_check_scc_error(struct tmio_mmc_host *host)
 {
 	struct renesas_sdhi *priv = host_to_priv(host);
 
+	if (!(host->mmc->ios.timing == MMC_TIMING_UHS_SDR104) &&
+	    !(host->mmc->ios.timing == MMC_TIMING_MMC_HS200) &&
+	    !(host->mmc->ios.timing == MMC_TIMING_MMC_HS400 &&
+	    !(priv->quirks && priv->quirks->hs400_4taps)))
+		return false;
+
 	/* Check SCC error */
 	if (sd_scc_read32(host, priv, SH_MOBILE_SDHI_SCC_RVSCNTL) &
 	    SH_MOBILE_SDHI_SCC_RVSCNTL_RVSEN &&
